        <h1>Best Dog Food for Senior Dogs</h1>
        <p><strong>Updated 2026</strong></p>

        <img src="../images/blog/senior-dog-food.webp"
             alt="Senior dog eating healthy food"
             width="800"
             height="500"
             loading="eager"
             style="margin: 20px 0; border-radius:10px;">

        <p>As dogs get older, their nutrition needs change. Senior dogs need food that supports joints, digestion, heart health, and weight control.</p>

        <p>If your dog is 7 years or older, it may be time to switch to a senior formula.</p>

        <h2>What Makes a Good Senior Dog Food?</h2>

        <ul>
            <li>High-quality protein</li>
            <li>Glucosamine for joint support</li>
            <li>Omega-3 fatty acids</li>
            <li>Lower calories to prevent weight gain</li>
            <li>Easy-to-digest ingredients</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Top Recommended Senior Dog Foods</h2>

        <h3>1. Blue Buffalo Life Protection Senior</h3>
        <p>Great balance of protein and joint support ingredients. Real meat is the first ingredient.</p>
        <a href="#" class="btn-primary">Check Price</a>

        <h3>2. Hill's Science Diet Adult 7+</h3>
        <p>Vet-recommended brand with balanced nutrients for aging dogs.</p>
        <a href="#" class="btn-primary">Check Price</a>

        <h3>3. Purina Pro Plan Bright Mind</h3>
        <p>Designed to support brain health in senior dogs.</p>
        <a href="#" class="btn-primary">Check Price</a>

        <h2>Ingredients to Avoid</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Artificial colors</li>
            <li>Low-quality meat by-products</li>
            <li>Excess fillers like corn gluten</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to Switch to Senior Dog Food</h2>
        <p>Switch slowly over 7â€“10 days. Mix small amounts of new food into the old food to avoid stomach upset.</p>

        <h2>Final Thoughts</h2>
        <p>Choosing the right food can help your dog stay active and healthy in their golden years.</p>

        <p>Want more tips? Visit our <a href="../dogs.html">Dog Care section</a>.</p>

